Synopsis:
   repeat <count> <command>

Description:
   This command allows any command to be executed any number of times.  One
   possible use for REPEAT might be for warning messages from a script; the
   warning is repeated to get your attention.  However, the potential uses
   for this command are endless.

Examples:
   To very boldly display the time each hour:
      on ^timer "??:00*" {
         repeat 3 echo B*** The time is $0!!B
      }

See Also:
   repeat(8)

